title: Elephants Up Close
subTitle: African elephants have an extraordinary ability to find waterholes and communicate with each other.

title: River Monsters
subTitle: Jeremy Wade investigates a case in Nepal that sounds strangely familiar - a lone fisherman dragged off his feet and into a mountain river by the original river monster, the goonch catfish.

title: Big Cat Tales
subTitle: Jonathan discovers the secretive den site of Dada the lioness' newborn cubs. Meanwhile, Olare, the leopard, displays a rarely seen mating ritual.

title: Parenthood
subTitle: Water is essential to all life on Earth, but too much or too little can be disastrous. Parents must master timing to overcome freshwater's constant change and successfully raise the next generation.

title: Wildest Survival
subTitle: The remarkable defences that species have perfected to survive.

title: Africa's Hunters
subTitle: A younger and stronger leopard challenges Kamuti for her territory in the Luangwa Valley, where she has reigned for ten years.

title: Hot Life Africa
subTitle: Leopards live in all kinds of ecosystems, from the humid jungles of India to the driest regions of Africa. They can adapt to almost any climate and feed on over 100 different species.

title: Hot Life Africa
subTitle: Being thin, having black patches on light-coloured fur, hyperventilating and licking itself regularly to evaporate saliva are the cheetah's most effective tricks to cope with its scorching environment.
